The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, October 18, 2003 				Metro Recommends
				 																The Book				 																																	(Various)  The third in the Moments of Intimacy, Laughter and Kinship  collection, a worldwide competition of photographs, is dedicated  to children, with over 100 startling images, spanning six  continents and diverse cultures, celebrating the many faces  of childhood. The limited edition can be ordered at ruth.hamiltonhodderpq.com.  The Festival				 																																	(Around  town) Handmade candles, by various NGOs, are on display at  Sasha. Its a Diwali and Dhanteras special exhibition at Ice  Skating Rink. Lamps, gift items of wax and bamboo and more  are on sale at the Light Show, at The Address. At Idiyas Gallery,  its Illuminations, comprising paintings, sculptures and other  artworks.  The Seminar				 																																	(1,  Alipore Road, Oct 18, 9.30 pm) The Agri-Horticultural Society  of India, Sonata Foundation and the National Cadet Corps Directorate  have organised a seminar to create awareness on pollution,  health and good living. Manab Mukherjee, minister of environment  and IT development, will attend.  The album				 																																	(Neepabithi  Ghosh) For lovers of melody, this Puja offering from the young  artiste makes for soothing listening. Myagher Pyat Phuta  Koira, bringing together East Bengal idiom and guitar  strums, is a winner, as is the title song. 

